HEADWORD: nire
<hw>ni⟦egrave⟧re"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>chiffonnier</ets>, fem.
<ets>chiffonni⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, fr. <ets>chiffon</ets> rag, fr.
<ets>chiffe</ets> a rag, flimsy cloth.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
gathers rags and odds and ends; a ragpicker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A receptacle for rags or shreds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A movable and ornamental closet or piece of
furniture with shelves or drawers.</def> <rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

